article.headline: Seton Hall 101, Fairleigh Dickinson 70
article.story: NEWARK, N.J. -- Jeremy Hazell scored a career-high 35 points -- one of four Seton Hall players in double figures -- to lead the Pirates to a 101-70 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday night. Robert Mitchell added 24 points and a game-high 10 rebounds for the Pirates (9-3), who snapped a two-game losing streak. Eugene Harvey finished with 15 points and Jordan Theodore had 11 points. Sean Baptiste had 31 points and nine rebounds for FDU (1-9). The two teams traded baskets early on, but Seton Hall soon took the lead for good on a jumper by Mitchell with 15:28 remaining in the opening half. The Pirates held a 44-39 lead at the break, then broke the game open with a 17-0 run to start the second half.
